caption: Valentines dinner was amazing! Calamari appetizer was crispy and tasted fresh. First time trying a tomahawk steak, it was the perfect medium temperature, and so big it nearly took up half the table :) My boyfriend got the dinner special which was a squash soup, ribeye, and humita. Sangria had a good wine to fruit ratio. The service and atmosphere was pleasant, they made sure we felt comfortable/warm enough for outdoor dining. The setup had proper ventilation and heaters so I’d definitely recommend eating outside. Everything was so delicious, we look forward to coming back and trying the empanadas next time.

This is one of my favorite neighborhood spots for dinner. It has a great setup for COVID with a cute, warm front porch type dining area. I unfortunately arrived late for my reservation so we couldn’t get a table inside the porch area so the staff set up a table outside on the right side of the restaurant. So if you prefer an even more open air setup, this place can accommodate!  The food and wine here is incredible. I ordered the sizzling meat platter, which was rich, tender and flavorful. The empanadas here are also delicious and addicting. While at dinner we even overheard someone ordering 20 empanadas to go...  Overall highly recommend for a cozy date night since the food, service, and ambiance are all excellent!

Great heated outside eating area where you can stay warm without a coat on.  Friendly service, delicious Malbecs on the wine list and enjoyed the food.  The octopus and empanadas should always be ordered and a lot of options for steak for any meat eaters out there.  Can’t wait to come back.

Great little place! This is actually the first restaurant in NYC that my family came to together in 2017, so it was really cool to go back again together recently. The food here is really good, from the appetizers to the dessert. I started with a chickpea and kale salad, and the table also ordered ham and cheese empanadas along with calamari. I think my favorite of the three appetizers was the empanadas; they were huge, fresh and really good. The salad and calamari were both great, though, don’t get me wrong. For my main course I had the filet, and it came with an interesting sauce on it that actually turned to be really good. For dessert I’d recommend the dulce de leche crepes; they’re really tasty. Both the service and the ambiance here are pretty standout, which is certainly a plus. The one negative about Libertador, in my opinion, is that you have to submit an online request and wait a few days for your reservation. I think they’d be better served to use a service such as OpenTable to manage their reservations.
